      "id": 53444,
      "name": "Claude De Vetter",
      "username": "MedTechCD",
      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/57b2e6/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-06-22T18:15:18.815Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I rarely have a complete rest day. I do weekly have a recovery day where activity is limited to 60 to 75 min brisk walk at 6k/h.<br>\nBut I do very little high intensity. I\u00b4m mainly focussed on long events at top Z2 intensity. Both cycling and running.<br>\nUsual routine is 90-120 min Z2 for 5 days a week, one long (4 to 6 hours) and the recovery day above.<br>\nI do some tempo zone when I feel like I\u00b4m ready for it. That\u00b4s on average 3-4 times a month. Sometimes an unspecified number of short HIT intervals at the end of my usual routine. Very little planning, except for the couple of priority events. Mostly by feel and backed with HRV monitoring.</p>",
