      "id": 58350,
      "name": "Johnnybike",
      "username": "Johnnybike",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/johnnybike/{size}/3694_2.png",
      "created_at": "2024-09-19T01:45:52.189Z",
      "cooked": "<p>This is one of the facets of inputting details for a plan that troubles me.<br>\nI have been planning training every day for the last 5 years at least.</p>\n<p>In reality I actually train about 300 days a year so have about a day off a week on average but I don\u2019t train on holiday and have the normal bouts of sickness etc.  I may go 10-12 days continuously or just 2-2</p>\n<p>I don\u2019t schedule a break in but natural life events intervene.<br>\nSometimes after a busy day I feel tired so have a rest day.</p>\n<p>So generally if inputting availability details I say 7 days a week and 6-10 hours.</p>\n<p>Works for me.</p>",
